<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,1757,1967]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,517,1757,1783]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Distribution and habitat:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName box="[547,793,1757,1782]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Orthophytum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="humile">
<emphasis box="[547,793,1757,1782]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Orthophytum humile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from Cristália and Grão Mogol counties in the state of 
<collectingRegion box="[298,468,1794,1820]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
. It grows on humid or dry rocks near streams at 
<quantity box="[1078,1233,1794,1820]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.25" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="8.5" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="m" value="925.0" valueMax="1000.0" valueMin="850.0">850–1000 m</quantity>
elevation, often associated with termite mounts.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,1757,1967]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,537,1869,1895]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">IUCN conservation status:</emphasis>
—EN B1ab (iii, iv). 
<taxonomicName box="[792,1039,1869,1894]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Orthophytum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="humile">
<emphasis box="[792,1039,1869,1894]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Orthophytum humile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in an estimated area less than 
<quantity box="[210,314,1906,1932]" metricMagnitude="6" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="km" value="5000.0">5000 km</quantity>
<superScript attach="right" box="[315,323,1904,1918]" fontSize="6" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">2</superScript>
. A decline in the number of populations was observed, as well as a decrease in the quality of the habitat.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
